body{background:var(--bg);font-family:var(--font);padding:48px 24px;display:flex;justify-content:center}
.container{max-width:600px;width:100%}
.skeleton{background:var(--surface);border-radius:8px;position:relative;overflow:hidden}
.skeleton::after{content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--shimmer),transparent);animation:shimmer 1.5s ease-in-out infinite}
@keyframes shimmer{0%{transform:translateX(-100%)}100%{transform:translateX(100%)}}
.card{background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:16px;padding:24px;margin-bottom:16px}
.card .header{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin-bottom:20px}
.avatar{width:44px;height:44px;border-radius:50%}
.name{width:120px;height:14px;border-radius:6px}
.date{width:80px;height:10px;border-radius:6px;margin-top:8px}
.title{width:80%;height:18px;border-radius:6px;margin-bottom:12px}
.line{height:12px;border-radius:6px;margin-bottom:10px}
.line.short{width:60%}
.line.medium{width:85%}
.line.full{width:100%}
.image{width:100%;height:200px;border-radius:10px;margin-top:16px}
.actions{display:flex;gap:12px;margin-top:20px}
.actions .btn{width:80px;height:32px;border-radius:8px}
@media(prefers-reduced-motion:reduce){.skeleton::after{animation:none}}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
  <div class="card">
    <div class="header"><div class="skeleton avatar"></div><div><div class="skeleton name"></div><div class="skeleton date"></div></div></div>
    <div class="skeleton title"></div>
    <div class="skeleton line full"></div>
    <div class="skeleton line medium"></div>
    <div class="skeleton line short"></div>
    <div class="skeleton image"></div>
    <div class="actions"><div class="skeleton btn"></div><div class="skeleton btn"></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="header"><div class="skeleton avatar"></div><div><div class="skeleton name"></div><div class="skeleton date"></div></div></div>
    <div class="skeleton title"></div>
    <div class="skeleton line full"></div>
    <div class="skeleton line short"></div>
  </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
```

The shimmer is a single pseudo-element translateX animation — GPU composited, performant. Matches the layout of the real content (avatar, name, title, paragraphs, image, action buttons) so the transition from skeleton to content feels seamless. Respects prefers-reduced-motion.

The issue is that most IntersectionObserver implementations call `unobserve()` after the first trigger. Remove that and the animation will replay.

But there's a subtlety — you need to REMOVE the class when the element leaves, so it can re-animate when it enters again:

```javascript
// CURRENT (triggers once):
const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
  entries.forEach(e => {
    if (e.isIntersecting) {
      e.target.classList.add('visible');
      observer.unobserve(e.target); // ← This prevents re-trigger
    }
  });
});

// FIXED (triggers every time):
const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
  entries.forEach(e => {
    if (e.isIntersecting) {
      e.target.classList.add('visible');
    } else {
      e.target.classList.remove('visible'); // ← Reset when leaving
    }
    // No unobserve — keep watching
  });
}, { threshold: 0.15 });
```

And the CSS needs to handle both states:
```css
.card {
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateY(20px);
  transition: opacity 0.5s ease, transform 0.5s ease;
}
.card.visible {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateY(0);
}
```

Using `transition` instead of `@keyframes` makes it reversible — the element fades out when scrolling away and fades back in when scrolling back.

